|WKO=====================================================================
|YKODarkflow is Darkwind's official web client. Point a browser at
|WKBplay.darkwind.ai|YKO and play -- nothing to install. It is a real
terminal with everything telnet offers, plus a graphical layer driven
by the game itself.

Panels: dockable panels for vitals, stats, worth, an XP monitor, your
room and an illustrated room image, inventory, group, chat, quests,
achievements, buffs, the sky, fishing, and more. Drag panels into the
side docks or float them; your layout is remembered between sessions.

Live map: a graphical tile map built from the exploration of all
players. Click any room on the map and the client walks you there
step by step, verifying each step with the game before taking the
next.

Area maps: |YKBareas map <number>|YKO opens a cataloged area's map for
browsing in its own Area Map pane, separate from the live map. See
|CKBareas|YKO.

Sound: game-driven sound effects and ambient audio, with volume and
mute controls.

Help: help topics open in a pop-up window instead of scrolling away
in your terminal.

Automation: aliases, triggers, highlights, and scripts, plus settings
export and import as JSON. See |CKBalias|YKO and |CKBscripts|YKO.

Comfort: dark and light themes, command history, tab completion, and
screenreader support (see |CKBscreenreader|YKO).|XX0

